public class MostRecentList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<T>

This implements a collection that can update according to most recent use.
New items will be added at index 0 and all items already in
it will be pushed down. The oldest item may be deleted if the
list is already at capacity.
If an item is added that is already in the list it will be
moved to the top of the list.
Removing an item from the list has the same behavior as
in a normal linked list.

Author:
soh
